From: OpenWRT Developer
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: ipq6018: enable all CPU frequencies for all speed bins

The IPQ6018 DTS restricts some higher CPU frequencies to specific speed bins
via opp-supported-hw bitmask. This causes legitimate chips to be unable to
run at their full rated frequencies (e.g., 1608MHz, 1800MHz).

The CPR4 regulator reads actual voltage limits from fuses, so there's no
risk of running at unsupported voltages. Enable all frequencies for all
speed bins by setting opp-supported-hw = <0x7> everywhere.

Note: The opp-microvolt values (1-8) are placeholders for CPR4 corner IDs,
not actual voltages. The CPR4 driver translates these to real voltages
based on fuse data.

Signed-off-by: OpenWRT Developer
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq6018.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq6018.dtsi
@@ -125,42 +125,42 @@
 		opp-1200000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1200000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <3>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x4>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 
 		opp-1320000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1320000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <4>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x3>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 
 		opp-1440000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1440000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <5>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x3>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 
 		opp-1512000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1512000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <6>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x3>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 
 		opp-1608000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1608000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <7>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x3>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 
 		opp-1800000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1800000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <8>;
-			opp-supported-hw = <0x3>;
+			opp-supported-hw = <0x7>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <200000>;
 		};
 	};
